02/09/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A UN spokesman announced on Monday (1 September) that a Serb man has died from his wounds, following a grenade attack in an ethnically mixed village. Milomir Savic, 35, was taken to a US military hospital at Camp Bondsteel late Sunday. Three other Serbs were injured in the attack. There are reports that KFOR troops combing the area after the blasts seized weapons.
In other news, the UN and KFOR announced the beginning of a one-month weapons collection campaign. Those who turn in their guns by 1 October will not be questioned or punished. (AP, Reuters, AFP - 01/09/03)
